PanopticDataSeam::mintBurnThroughInterface
├── given a borrowed Panoptic pool deployed via the factory choreography referenced only as IPanopticData with collateral via IERC4626
│   └── it should compile with the helper-returned address consumed as IPanopticData so forge build is green the compile-time proof
├── when one position is minted via IPanopticData dispatch with stored balance zero so it mints
│   ├── it should not revert
│   └── it should read a PositionBalance array of length one via getAccumulatedFeesAndPositionsData
└── when the same position is dispatched with size zero so it burns
    └── it should close the position and a subsequent read reflects the burn
